      • add

        public boolean add(T element)
        The add method will take an instance of the type variable T as a parameter element, and it will insert it at the correct place within the list using element's compareTo method. This method should not allow null elements or duplicates to be added to the list. The method returns true if successful and false otherwise. The method does NOT throw exceptions in case the argument is null or the element already exists.
